<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="932" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d932">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Eddy</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-10-04"><hi rend="italic">October 4,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Adee states that the people of the United States are thrilled with
                            horror by the kidnaping of Miss Stone, and directs Mr. Eddy to say to
                            the Porte that the Government of the United States urgently requests it
                            to use its utmost efforts to effect her rescue.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>